{"html":"<p>I made a simple Firefox add-on that hides <em>most</em> articles about COVID-19.\nThe tool uses basic text matching to identify posts about SARS-CoV-2 and its consequences.\nIt gained some traction on <a class=\"link\" href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=22781113\">Hacker&nbsp;News</a>.</p>\n<figure>\n<figcaption>Phagocyte <strong>Demo</strong></figcaption>\n<img src=\"portfolio/phagocyte/demo.png\" alt=\"Demo\"/>\n</figure>\n\n\n<p><span class=\"meta\">Try it out!</span>\n<a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/firefox/addon/phagocyte/\" class=\"link\">Download link\n<svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" class=\"icon icon-inline\"><use xlink:href=\"icons/sprite.svg#link\"/></svg></a></p>\n<p><span class=\"meta\">Source Code:</span>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/LenaSchnedlitz/phagocyte\" class=\"link\">GitHub\n<svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" class=\"icon icon-inline\"><use xlink:href=\"icons/sprite.svg#link\"/></svg></a></p>\n","slug":"phagocyte","rank":6,"title":"Phagocyte","teaser":"Hide articles about COVID-19 in Firefox.","previewType":"png","background":"primary-dark","align":"left"}